The paper deals with the application of deep learning to the domain of digital pathology, specifically the task of quantifying prognostic features in colorectal cancer. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
